comments.text:
This is probably one of the most insightful comedy sketches that I have 
seen in a long time. However this comedy sketch does not focus on one dirty 
secret, which women don't want to fess up to That secret is that women are 
in large part responsible for perpetrating this double standard with 
respect to age and gender. It is popular  among feminists to describe this 
as solely a  problem with a male run Hollywood and patriarchal media 
fostering this double standard, but out in real middle class America, many 
women tend to naturally aim for men older than them, especially because 
many older men are wealthier than younger men and are far more emotionally 
mature and stable. The result is a natural expectation by both men and 
women, that if one gender is still desirable when they are older, it will 
be men and not women. Secondly, men, when they take care of themselves, do 
tend to age better than women. This is an unfortunate fact of nature that 
only the most delusional will deny. The higher testosterone levels that men 
have, which give them skin that is more resilient and gives them muscle 
mass, while declining in their 40s and 50s, does not decline anywhere near 
to the degree that a woman's estrogen level declines - the very hormone 
women need to look youthful. Finally, it does make sense, from an 
evolutionary perspective, why men are considered to be far more desirable 
as they get older than women do at the same age. Men retain their fertility 
longer. Most healthy men in their 60s, 70s, and even 80s can impregnate a 
woman. A woman's fertility rate, after 37 years of age, drops 
precipitously, and very few can have children after the age of 45 without 
costly medical intervention. Hence, from a standpoint of species survival, 
it make sense that the gender with greatest longevity in terms of fertility 
would also be the one that retains their desirability the longest.﻿
